article.headline: Coppin St 58, Norfolk State 54
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Tywain McKee had 34 points, including two free throws that helped seal Coppin State's 58-54 victory over Norfolk State on Saturday night. Coppin State (9-14, 9-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) led by as many as nine in the second half before Karandick Ogunride's layup with 1:58 to go gave Norfolk State their first lead of the half, 54-53. He was fouled on the shot, but missed the point after attempt. Al'Davon Thomas missed another free throw attempt, then a turnover by Brian Falcon opened the door for Talmadge Bell's 3-pointer that put Coppin State back on top for good with 38 seconds left. McKee's two free throws with 11 seconds left sealed the win. Neither team led by more than four in the first half, which saw nine of the game's 11 lead changes. Darryl Proctor led Coppin State with 14 rebounds, 12 of which were defensive, but Norfolk State outrebounded the Eagles 47-33. The Spartans had 18 second-chance points to Coppin State's 6. Norfolk State also outperformed Coppin State in the paint, outscoring the Eagles 38-16. Ogunride had 16 rebounds for the Spartans (8-14, 7-5), 10 on the defensive side. Calvin Brown led Norfolk State with 14 points and Thomas added 12.
